and knowledge sharing and mentoring, as well as promotes team cohesion.

What to look for in a code review? Try to look for things such as ğ—±ğ—²ğ˜€ğ—¶ğ—´ğ—» (does this integrate well with the rest of the system and are interactions of different
components make sense), ğ—³ğ˜‚ğ—»ğ—°ğ˜ğ—¶ğ—¼ğ—»ğ—®ğ—¹ğ—¶ğ˜ğ˜† (does this change is what the developer intended), ğ—°ğ—¼ğ—ºğ—½ğ—¹ğ—²ğ˜…ğ—¶ğ˜ğ˜† (is this code more complex than it should be), ğ—»ğ—®ğ—ºğ—¶ğ—»ğ—´ (is naming good?),
